Creational Patterns - Factory Pattern
======================================

  In another words it is a factory of classes. In simple words if we having a super class and n-subclasses 
  and based on data provided, we have to return the object of one of the sub-classes, we can use factory pattern.
  
When to use a Factory Pattern?
==============================

  1. When a class does not know which class of object it must create
  2. In programmers language, you can use factory pattern where you have to create an 
     object of any on of sub-classes depending on the data provided.
